  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). Validation evidence is drawn from the Morrison et al. bench study, which systematically characterised pump-induced haemolysis across five flow-speed operating points. The study is cited throughout as satisfying the controlled-experiment requirement for the validation activity, providing paired inlet/outlet blood sampling under rigorously defined pump conditions — readers are directed to Table 3 of the source publication for the experimental protocol details.",
