      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/req/hemolysis-validation-req",
      "type": "Requirement",
      "name": "Haemolysis validation — controlled-experiment requirement",
      "description": "Per the V&V plan for this COU, validation of CFD-predicted haemolysis must be supported by a controlled experiment in which all relevant independent variables (flow rate, rotational speed, fluid properties) are actively manipulated by the investigator and confounding factors are formally controlled through randomisation or equivalent means. This requirement ensures that causal inference from bench data to model fidelity is defensible.",
      "requiredVerificationMethod": "controlled-experiment"
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/activity/morrison-bench-study",
      "type": "Activity",
      "name": "Morrison et al. bench haemolysis characterisation study",
      "description": "Bench study in which the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump was operated at five flow-speed combinations under CPB-representative conditions. Blood samples were collected from the circuit and analysed for plasma-free haemoglobin. Operating conditions were set by the investigator, but the study was conducted without a formal randomisation protocol, blinding, or concurrent control arm. Donor-to-donor variability, ambient temperature, and circuit priming effects were not formally controlled. The study is best characterised as an observational study of pump performance under specified nominal conditions rather than a controlled experiment in the methodological sense.",
      "activityType": "observational-study"
    }
